g1101.definition: [γλωσσόκομον] from {{g1100}} and the base of {{g2889}}; properly, a case (to keep mouthpieces of wind-instruments in) i.e. (by extension) a casket or (specially) purse

g1102.definition: [γναφεύς] by variation for a derivative from κνάπτω (to tease cloth); a cloth-dresser

g1103.definition: [γνήσιος] from the same as {{g1077}}; legitimate (of birth), i.e. genuine

g1105.definition: [γνόφος] akin to {{g3509}}; gloom (as of a storm)

g1106.definition: [γνώμη] from {{g1097}}; cognition, i.e. (subjectively) opinion, or (objectively) resolve (counsel, consent, etc.)

g1107.definition: [γνωρίζω] from a derivative of {{g1097}}; to make known; subjectively, to know

g1108.definition: [γνῶσις] from {{g1097}}; knowing (the act), i.e. (by implication) knowledge

g1114.definition: [γόης] from γοάω (to wail); properly, a wizard (as muttering spells), i.e. (by implication) an imposter

g1115.definition: [Γολγοθᾶ] of Chaldee origin (compare {{h1538}}); the skull; Golgotha, a knoll near Jerusalem

g1116.definition: [Γόμοῤῥα] of Hebrew origin ({{h6017}}); Gomorrha (i.e. Amorah), a place near the Dead Sea

g1117.definition: [γόμος] from {{g1073}}; a load (as filling), i.e. (specially) a cargo, or (by extension) wares

g1118.definition: [γονεύς] from the base of {{g1096}}; a parent

g1120.definition: [γονυπετέω] from a compound of {{g1119}} and the alternate of {{g4098}}; to fall on the knee

g1121.definition: [γράμμα] from {{g1125}}; a writing, i.e. a letter, note, epistle, book, etc.; plural learning

g1122.definition: [γραμματεύς] from {{g1121}}. a writer, i.e. (professionally) scribe or secretary

g1124.definition: [γραφή] from {{g1125}}; a document, i.e. holy Writ (or its contents or a statement in it)

g1125.definition: [γράφω] a primary verb; to "grave", especially to write; figuratively, to describe

g1126.definition: [γραώδης] from γραύς (an old woman) and {{g1491}}; crone-like, i.e. silly

g1127.definition: [γρηγορεύω] from {{g1453}}; to keep awake, i.e. watch (literally or figuratively)

g1128.definition: [γυμνάζω] from {{g1131}}; to practise naked (in the games), i.e. train (figuratively)

g1130.definition: [γυμνητεύω] from a derivative of {{g1131}}; to strip, i.e. (reflexively) go poorly clad

g1131.definition: [γυμνός] of uncertain affinity; nude (absolute or relative, literal or figurative)

g1133.definition: [γυναικάριον] a diminutive from {{g1135}}; a little (i.e. foolish) woman

g1135.definition: [γυνή] probably from the base of {{g1096}}; a woman; specially, a wife

g1136.definition: [Γώγ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1463}}); Gog, a symbolic name for some future Antichrist

g1138.definition: [Δαβίδ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1732}}); Dabid (i.e. David), the Israelite king

g1139.definition: [δαιμονίζομαι] middle voice from {{g1142}}; to be exercised by a dæmon

g1140.definition: [δαιμόνιον] neuter of a derivative of {{g1142}}; a dæmonic being; by extension a deity

g1142.definition: [δαίμων] from δαίω (to distribute fortunes); a dæmon or supernatural spirit (of a bad nature)

g1143.definition: [δάκνω] a prolonged form of a primary root; to bite, i.e. (figuratively) thwart

g1144.definition: [δάκρυ]   or δάκρυονof uncertain affinity; a tear

g1148.definition: [Δαλμανουθά] probably of Chaldee origin; Dalmanutha, a place in Palestine

g1149.definition: [Δαλματία] probably of foreign derivation; Dalmatia, a region of Europe

g1150.definition: [δαμάζω] a variation of an obsolete primary of the same meaning; to tame

g1151.definition: [δάμαλις] probably from the base of {{g1150}}; a heifer (as tame)

g1152.definition: [Δάμαρις] probably from the base of {{g1150}}; perhaps gentle; Damaris, an Athenian woman

g1153.definition: [Δαμασκηνός] from {{g1154}}; a Damascene or inhabitant of Damascus

g1154.definition: [Δαμασκός] of Hebrew origin ({{h1834}}); Damascus, a city of Syria

g1155.definition: [δανείζω] from {{g1156}}; to loan on interest; reflexively, to borrow

g1156.definition: [δάνειον] from δάνος (a gift); probably akin to the base of {{g1325}}; a loan

g1158.definition: [Δανιήλ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1840}}); Daniel, an Israelite

g1159.definition: [δαπανάω] from {{g1160}}; to expend, i.e. (in a good sense) to incur cost, or (in a bad one) to waste

g1161.definition: [δέ] a primary particle (adversative or continuative); but, and, etc.

g1163.definition: [δεῖ] 3rd person singular active present of {{g1210}}; also deon deh-on'; neuter active participle of the same; both used impersonally; it is (was, etc.) necessary (as binding)

g1164.definition: [δεῖγμα] from the base of {{g1166}}; a specimen (as shown)

g1166.definition: [δεικνύω] a prolonged form of an obsolete primary of the same meaning; to show (literally or figuratively)

g1169.definition: [δειλός] from δεός (dread); timid, i.e. (by implication) faithless

g1170.definition: [δεῖνα] probably from the same as {{g1171}} (through the idea of forgetting the name as fearful, i.e. strange); so and so (when the person is not specified)

g1171.definition: [δεινῶς] adverb from a derivative of the same as {{g1169}}; terribly, i.e. excessively

g1172.definition: [δειπνέω] from {{g1173}}; to dine, i.e. take the principle (or evening) meal

g1173.definition: [δεῖπνον] from the same as {{g1160}}; dinner, i.e. the chief meal (usually in the evening)

g1174.definition: [δεισιδαιμονέστερος] the compound of a derivative of the base of {{g1169}} and {{g1142}}; more religious than others

g1177.definition: [δεκαδύο] from {{g1176}} and {{g1417}}; two and ten, i.e. twelve

g1178.definition: [δεκαπέντε] from {{g1176}} and {{g4002}}; ten and five, i.e. fifteen

g1179.definition: [Δεκάπολις] from {{g1176}} and {{g4172}}; the ten-city region; the Decapolis, a district in Syria

g1180.definition: [δεκατέσσαρες] from {{g1176}} and {{g5064}}; ten and four, i.e. fourteen

g1181.definition: [δεκάτη] feminine of {{g1182}}; a tenth, i.e. as a percentage or (technically) tithe

g1183.definition: [δεκατόω] from {{g1181}}; to tithe, i.e. to give or take a tenth

g1185.definition: [δελεάζω] from the base of {{g1388}}; to entrap, i.e. (figuratively) delude

g1186.definition: [δένδρον] probably from δρύς (an oak); a tree

g1187.definition: [δεξιολάβος] from {{g1188}} and {{g2983}}; a guardsman (as if taking the right) or light-armed soldier

g1188.definition: [δεξιός] from {{g1209}}; the right side or (feminine) hand (as that which usually takes)

g1189.definition: [δέομαι] middle voice of {{g1210}}; to beg (as binding oneself), i.e. petition Compare {{g4441}}.

g1190.definition: [Δερβαῖος] from {{g1191}}; a Derbæan or inhabitant of Derbe

g1191.definition: [Δέρβη] of foreign origin; Derbe, a place in Asia Minor

g1194.definition: [δέρω] a primary verb; properly, to flay, i.e. (by implication) to scourge, or (by analogy) to thrash

g1195.definition: [δεσμεύω] from a (presumed) derivative of {{g1196}}; to be a binder (captor), i.e. to enchain (a prisoner), to tie on (a load)

g1199.definition: [δεσμόν]   or δεσμόςneuter and masculine respectively from {{g1210}}; a band, i.e. ligament (of the body) or shackle (of a prisoner); figuratively, an impediment or disability

g1200.definition: [δεσμοφύλαξ] from {{g1199}} and {{g5441}}; a jailer (as guarding the prisoners)
